WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.795 --> 00:00:05.923
[rain pattering]

2
00:00:06.006 --> 00:00:08.759
[siren wailing]

3
00:00:30.864 --> 00:00:32.032
[thunder rumbling]

4
00:00:33.200 --> 00:00:34.618
You can finish that.

5
00:00:47.089 --> 00:00:49.091
You think I'm doing
the wrong thing? Leaving?

6
00:00:49.174 --> 00:00:51.969
I've got problems of my own.
I don't think about you 24 hours a day.

7
00:00:52.052 --> 00:00:53.845
I know that. I know. I just…

8
00:00:56.890 --> 00:00:59.768
I was talking to everybody. and I…

9
00:01:02.562 --> 00:01:05.440
I looked at Marcus's face.
and I felt like a piece of shit.

10
00:01:05.524 --> 00:01:07.377
Yeah. well. you should feel
like a piece of shit. You quit.

11
00:01:07.401 --> 00:01:09.570
That's what I'm saying.
Maybe I shouldn't leave. right?

12
00:01:09.653 --> 00:01:11.154
No. no. no.

13
00:01:12.864 --> 00:01:14.408
You should definitely leave.

14
00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:16.910
But you should also feel bad.

15
00:01:16.994 --> 00:01:19.913
And Marcus is the fucking man.
He doesn't need you. but…

16
00:01:21.790 --> 00:01:23.458
All those things are true.

17
00:01:24.001 --> 00:01:25.544
I don't know. it's just…

18
00:01:26.336 --> 00:01:28.463
Syd's got me prepping. right?

19
00:01:29.172 --> 00:01:31.592
-Just cutting onions.
-Really?

20
00:01:34.261 --> 00:01:37.514
And I've got this feeling that I had
when I first started in restaurants.

21
00:01:37.598 --> 00:01:39.808
right. where I wasn't thinking
about anything else.

22
00:01:39.891 --> 00:01:43.895
I wasn't thinking about stars
or temperatures or-or time.

23
00:01:44.688 --> 00:01:48.942
It's an onion. and I could do that.
Just prep for everybody. you know?

24
00:01:49.026 --> 00:01:50.861
And not have to think about anything.

25
00:01:54.823 --> 00:01:55.991
That sounds awful.

26
00:01:57.868 --> 00:01:59.578
And that would last for. like. ten seconds

27
00:01:59.661 --> 00:02:01.913
and then you'd turn into
a fucking psycho again.

28
00:02:04.249 --> 00:02:06.918
And I think that the reason you like
being in those kitchens

29
00:02:07.002 --> 00:02:09.355
where you didn't have to think about shit
was 'cause there was so much shit

30
00:02:09.379 --> 00:02:10.922
you didn't wanna think about.

31
00:02:11.006 --> 00:02:13.568
And not thinking about yourself
all the time. that's a good thing.

32
00:02:13.592 --> 00:02:16.094
but not thinking about anything
is fucking depressing.

33
00:02:18.472 --> 00:02:22.893
Additionally. like. you're not.
like. a great teammate.

34
00:02:24.895 --> 00:02:26.146
The fuck does that mean?

35
00:02:26.229 --> 00:02:29.983
You know. you're always alone. you know?

36
00:02:30.651 --> 00:02:33.612
That's not even true.
I've worked in kitchens my entire life.

37
00:02:33.695 --> 00:02:37.240
Yeah. and you just shouted at everybody
'cause you're. like. differently abled.

38
00:02:37.324 --> 00:02:41.536
That's not collaborating. you know?
You never played sports. You don't get it.

39
00:02:42.204 --> 00:02:43.372
I wrestled in high school.

40
00:02:43.455 --> 00:02:45.415
That's solo. you know?

41
00:02:45.499 --> 00:02:48.418
And you did that for a month.
and you got the shit beat out of you.

42
00:02:49.544 --> 00:02:50.921
When I call you differently abled.

43
00:02:51.004 --> 00:02:53.632
I wasn't. like. trying to be mean
or call you a re…

44
00:02:53.715 --> 00:02:55.276
-You know. the R word.
-I understand. I know.

45
00:02:55.300 --> 00:02:56.385
I know what you mean.

46
00:03:00.806 --> 00:03:04.685
Doing something where you have to think
about other people and other things.

47
00:03:06.269 --> 00:03:07.854
that would be good for you.

48
00:03:10.524 --> 00:03:12.025
I should turn right.

49
00:03:12.109 --> 00:03:14.027
Yeah. I don't know
what the fuck that means.

50
00:03:14.111 --> 00:03:16.738
Just be a team player. you know?

51
00:03:16.822 --> 00:03:18.281
Be a fucking human being.

52
00:03:19.157 --> 00:03:22.619
Ask somebody how they're doing.
Tell them they're nice. I don't know.

53
00:03:24.246 --> 00:03:25.539
That makes sense.

54
00:03:31.378 --> 00:03:32.587
How are you doing?

55
00:03:33.505 --> 00:03:34.923
-Me?
-Yeah.

56
00:03:36.925 --> 00:03:38.135
I'm struggling.

57
00:03:41.513 --> 00:03:43.181
Thank you for asking.

58
00:03:45.225 --> 00:03:46.601
Sorry to hear that.

59
00:03:46.685 --> 00:03:47.686
It's all good.

60
00:03:47.769 --> 00:03:49.062
I'll prevail.

61
00:03:49.688 --> 00:03:50.689
Yeah.

62
00:03:51.731 --> 00:03:53.859
I got in a little fucking
car accident this morning.

63
00:03:53.942 --> 00:03:55.152
Fuck. Really?

64
00:03:55.235 --> 00:03:57.279
It was stupid. I wasn't paying attention.

65
00:03:57.362 --> 00:04:00.782
I was thinking about this one time when
I slapped the shit out of your brother.

66
00:04:00.866 --> 00:04:02.409
I've been thinking about that all day.

67
00:04:02.492 --> 00:04:03.869
Fuck.

68
00:04:03.952 --> 00:04:06.371
Yeah. man. I think about that shit.
like. all the time.

69
00:04:06.455 --> 00:04:07.456
I mean…

70
00:04:08.415 --> 00:04:10.041
look where the fuck we are.

71
00:04:14.004 --> 00:04:15.505
You don't got to say anything.

72
00:04:17.883 --> 00:04:19.217
And I gotta focus anyway.

73
00:04:19.301 --> 00:04:23.180
I gotta restore some morale here
with a fucking barn burner of a pre-meal.

74
00:04:23.263 --> 00:04:24.931
and I got nothing in the tank.

75
00:04:25.015 --> 00:04:28.059
It's all right. You don't gotta put
too much pressure on it. you know?

76
00:04:28.143 --> 00:04:31.813
Do you remember any that.
like. you know. got you really fired up?

77
00:04:32.397 --> 00:04:34.024
You just gotta be honest.

78
00:04:36.151 --> 00:04:38.570
You know. don't read
some bullshit quote. Just…

79
00:04:40.739 --> 00:04:41.823
level with everybody.

80
00:04:41.907 --> 00:04:44.701
Real. passionate.
That makes you want to kill.

81
00:04:48.580 --> 00:04:49.581
Heard.

82
00:04:51.625 --> 00:04:56.213
I'm gonna go drill some onions. but.
um. thank you for listening. you know.

83
00:04:58.173 --> 00:04:59.174
Also.

84
00:04:59.966 --> 00:05:00.967
Mikey…

85
00:05:04.846 --> 00:05:06.097
He had it coming.

86
00:05:07.265 --> 00:05:09.684
Yeah. he did. He did.

87
00:05:11.770 --> 00:05:12.771
But…

88
00:05:13.563 --> 00:05:15.398
You know. I wish that it wasn't me.

89
00:05:21.154 --> 00:05:22.489
I'm glad that it was. All right?

90
00:05:22.572 --> 00:05:24.407
[chuckles] Yeah. yeah.

91
00:05:26.409 --> 00:05:27.494
[Carmy groans]

92
00:05:28.870 --> 00:05:30.914
[Sydney] Can somebody
please bring that tarp?

93
00:05:30.997 --> 00:05:33.959
This is insane.
if anybody wants to help clean.

94
00:05:34.543 --> 00:05:37.170
Teddy. you okay. honey?

95
00:05:37.254 --> 00:05:39.047
Mostly just sad now. to be honest.

96
00:05:39.130 --> 00:05:40.674
-Teddy. hang tight. bro.
-[Ted] Okay.

97
00:05:40.757 --> 00:05:42.610
I'm gonna dry it up down here.
I'm gonna get you down.

98
00:05:42.634 --> 00:05:44.302
-[Ted] Okay.
-Ted. how we doing?

99
00:05:44.386 --> 00:05:45.804
[Ted] Not good.

100
00:05:45.887 --> 00:05:47.556
Yeah. that sucks. dog.

101
00:05:47.639 --> 00:05:48.932
[Ted] Hey. Syd. Carm.

102
00:05:49.015 --> 00:05:50.183
-Yo.
-Yeah?

103
00:05:50.684 --> 00:05:51.852
[Ted] You guys mad at me?

104
00:05:52.936 --> 00:05:55.105
-It's not your fault.
-A little. to be honest.

105
00:05:55.188 --> 00:05:56.982
Pastry's a little bit mad.

106
00:05:57.566 --> 00:06:00.443
Fuck this. Fuck everything.
Jesus fucking Christ.

107
00:06:00.527 --> 00:06:03.029
-[knocking]
-[Sugar] Yeah. Hi. [inhales deeply]

108
00:06:03.113 --> 00:06:04.713
Just checking on you. You need anything?

109
00:06:04.781 --> 00:06:06.199
Uh…

110
00:06:06.283 --> 00:06:07.742
That's nice. Thank you.

111
00:06:07.826 --> 00:06:09.619
-[Carmy] Yeah.
-Um…

112
00:06:10.495 --> 00:06:12.205
We're barely gonna cover payroll.

113
00:06:12.706 --> 00:06:15.959
[clicks tongue]
And that is with the slashed menu.

114
00:06:16.042 --> 00:06:18.378
the labor reductions. canceled orders.

115
00:06:18.461 --> 00:06:22.507
But. uh. Susie. Laura. and Brendan.
they saved us some money. so that's good.

116
00:06:22.591 --> 00:06:24.050
[inhales deeply. sighs]

117
00:06:24.134 --> 00:06:26.845
-Who the fuck are Susan and Brendy and...
-Servers. Carm.

118
00:06:26.928 --> 00:06:27.929
They all quit.

119
00:06:28.513 --> 00:06:29.973
-[Sugar] Yeah.
-Right.

120
00:06:32.058 --> 00:06:34.436
Talk to Neil. He's sad you're leaving.

121
00:06:36.062 --> 00:06:37.230
Yeah. I know.

122
00:06:40.734 --> 00:06:43.737
[Sugar inhales deeply. sighs]

123
00:06:47.699 --> 00:06:49.326
[Carmy sighs]

124
00:06:53.246 --> 00:06:54.456
How's the. um…

125
00:06:54.539 --> 00:06:55.790
-Whatever.
-This?

126
00:06:55.874 --> 00:06:58.335
-Yeah. yeah.
-Is it… is it crazy?

127
00:06:58.918 --> 00:07:03.214
I mean. are you looking
for something bad to happen?

128
00:07:03.298 --> 00:07:06.968
No. it's-it's a compulsion.
Like. I-I have to listen.

129
00:07:07.052 --> 00:07:09.638
I cannot not be listening right now.

130
00:07:09.721 --> 00:07:14.184
and it's like I want her to do
something fucked-up. you know?

131
00:07:17.270 --> 00:07:18.688
Yeah. no. I know the feeling.

132
00:07:21.691 --> 00:07:23.109
She's not going to.

133
00:07:25.278 --> 00:07:26.488
No.

134
00:07:26.571 --> 00:07:27.697
[Sugar] No.

135
00:07:32.243 --> 00:07:33.703
I'm really tired. Carmen.

136
00:07:40.001 --> 00:07:43.380
You want to give me the… the thing?
I can listen for a little bit.

137
00:07:44.756 --> 00:07:45.882
Really?

138
00:07:45.965 --> 00:07:47.717
Yeah. if you got something you want to…

139
00:07:47.801 --> 00:07:49.052
Y-Yeah. I got plenty.

140
00:07:49.135 --> 00:07:51.012
-[Carmy] Okay.
-Okay. thank you.

141
00:07:51.096 --> 00:07:52.722
-Let's see.
-[Sugar] That's awesome.

142
00:07:53.348 --> 00:07:54.349
Um…

143
00:07:54.432 --> 00:07:56.101
-Yeah. so it's right here.
-Okay.

144
00:07:56.184 --> 00:07:58.144
And if she does anything remotely weird.

145
00:07:58.228 --> 00:07:59.872
-you'll find me.
-Yeah. no. I'll tell her not to.

146
00:07:59.896 --> 00:08:01.336
-and I'll find you.
-Okay. thank you.

147
00:08:01.398 --> 00:08:02.607
-Okay.
-Okay.

148
00:08:04.317 --> 00:08:07.529
[Donna] Yeah. Yes. baby. What. what?

149
00:08:09.239 --> 00:08:11.116
Oh. oh. You want that.

150
00:08:12.450 --> 00:08:14.536
[Carmy sighs. tuts]

151
00:08:14.619 --> 00:08:15.662
[Donna] Okay.

152
00:08:15.745 --> 00:08:18.289
[chuckles] Okay.

153
00:08:21.334 --> 00:08:23.002
[car horns honking]

154
00:08:23.837 --> 00:08:25.672
[phone ringing]

155
00:08:32.762 --> 00:08:34.347
You here for the street permit?

156
00:08:35.390 --> 00:08:37.392
No. Air rights.

157
00:08:39.686 --> 00:08:41.046
[clerk] Did you fill out the form?

158
00:08:41.104 --> 00:08:42.439
We just did.

159
00:08:42.522 --> 00:08:44.441
Yeah. so what do we do next?

160
00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:49.612
Hold on.

161
00:08:52.198 --> 00:08:53.992
One foot after another. You got it. buddy.

162
00:08:55.160 --> 00:08:57.203
You got it. You got it.
Okay. that's perfect.

163
00:08:57.287 --> 00:08:59.330
-His first time using the ladder.
-Oh. yeah.

164
00:08:59.414 --> 00:09:00.558
-[Chuckie] You got it.
-Got it.

165
00:09:00.582 --> 00:09:01.583
-You good?
-Yeah.

166
00:09:01.666 --> 00:09:02.667
You good?

167
00:09:03.626 --> 00:09:04.854
[Ted] I feel like that fucked me up.

168
00:09:04.878 --> 00:09:06.421
Feel like I gotta go see somebody.

169
00:09:06.504 --> 00:09:07.898
[Chi-Chi] I got you. baby. Go to Jill.

170
00:09:07.922 --> 00:09:09.608
-Who's Jill?
-[Chuckie. Chi-chi] Our therapist.

171
00:09:09.632 --> 00:09:12.052
-Their therapist.
-Gonna put this here. We're gonna need it.

172
00:09:12.135 --> 00:09:13.636
[Sydney groans]

173
00:09:13.720 --> 00:09:15.930
Ooh. Sorry. Behind. Okay.

174
00:09:16.014 --> 00:09:18.224
Hey. So the contractor
will be here tomorrow.

175
00:09:18.308 --> 00:09:20.028
-[chuckles]
-I know. I know. it's not ideal.

176
00:09:20.101 --> 00:09:22.145
-Tomorrow.
-[Sugar] Hey. You okay. baby boy?

177
00:09:22.228 --> 00:09:25.190
-I was up there for three hours.
-You were not up there for three hours.

178
00:09:28.109 --> 00:09:29.694
-You good?
-No.

179
00:09:29.778 --> 00:09:32.465
-Maybe helping might help you feel... Okay.
-I don't think I can carry on after that.

180
00:09:32.489 --> 00:09:36.242
Um. could you guys maybe help
with the… with the roof a little?

181
00:09:36.326 --> 00:09:38.036
-Yes. Chef.
-Thank you.

182
00:09:38.119 --> 00:09:39.412
-Yeah.
-Thank you so very much.

183
00:09:39.496 --> 00:09:41.247
-Eat that.
-Oh. I…

184
00:09:41.331 --> 00:09:43.625
I am allergic to apples.
Thank you so much though.

185
00:09:43.708 --> 00:09:45.168
-Eat that.
-I'm good right now.

186
00:09:56.137 --> 00:09:57.180
It's good.

187
00:09:59.265 --> 00:10:00.558
Thank you. Chef.

188
00:10:02.977 --> 00:10:04.020
All right.

189
00:10:05.271 --> 00:10:06.648
Focus. Rich.

190
00:10:08.441 --> 00:10:13.029
Paths to success

191
00:10:14.322 --> 00:10:15.698
by R.

192
00:10:18.076 --> 00:10:21.746
Jerimovich. Partner.

193
00:10:24.374 --> 00:10:25.458
All right.

194
00:10:26.126 --> 00:10:27.544
Tempo…

195
00:10:27.627 --> 00:10:29.212
[object shatters]

196
00:10:31.881 --> 00:10:32.921
[Tina] What are you doing?

197
00:10:32.966 --> 00:10:35.593
-I found more plates.
-[Tina] Oh. [sighs]

198
00:10:35.677 --> 00:10:37.470
You know you're an old lady.

199
00:10:37.554 --> 00:10:42.267
You're not supposed to be
carrying things with your bad legs.

200
00:10:42.350 --> 00:10:43.893
Don't tell Sydney I dropped one.

201
00:10:43.977 --> 00:10:45.937
-I would never tell her. Come on.
-[sighs]

202
00:10:46.479 --> 00:10:47.897
Hey.

203
00:10:47.981 --> 00:10:49.149
-Yo.
-All good?

204
00:10:49.232 --> 00:10:51.568
[Carmy] Yeah. yeah. all good.
Nothing to report.

205
00:10:51.651 --> 00:10:55.697
She. um. made a phone call
for a little bit.

206
00:10:55.780 --> 00:10:59.659
Was making cute baby voices.
so it's all… so it's all good.

207
00:11:00.326 --> 00:11:04.831
Well. hopefully today isn't enough time
for DD to stunt her emotional development.

208
00:11:04.914 --> 00:11:06.124
[Carmy] Mmm.

209
00:11:06.207 --> 00:11:09.419
-[clicks tongue] Was that a shot there?
-Oh. right between the eyes.

210
00:11:09.502 --> 00:11:11.254
-I have emotions.
-I know you do.

211
00:11:11.880 --> 00:11:12.881
I know.

212
00:11:12.964 --> 00:11:14.716
[rain pattering]

213
00:11:14.799 --> 00:11:15.800
[sighs]

214
00:11:17.760 --> 00:11:19.613
You know what I was thinking
about this morning?

215
00:11:19.637 --> 00:11:20.638
Mmm?

216
00:11:20.722 --> 00:11:22.557
How crazy it is that I just…

217
00:11:22.640 --> 00:11:25.935
I spent so much time
running from this place.

218
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:29.522
I fucking hated it so much.

219
00:11:31.149 --> 00:11:32.775
And now it's my favorite thing.

220
00:11:33.443 --> 00:11:34.777
Yeah. that makes sense.

221
00:11:35.945 --> 00:11:37.697
-"You made it nice."
-[Sugar] Oh.

222
00:11:37.780 --> 00:11:40.783
[imitates Donna]
"I made it nice for everyone. Carmen."

223
00:11:40.867 --> 00:11:42.052
I don't like it when you do that.

224
00:11:42.076 --> 00:11:44.287
-So scary. It's so scary.
-"Carmen!"

225
00:11:44.370 --> 00:11:45.371
[Sugar chuckles]

226
00:11:45.455 --> 00:11:47.040
[groans]

227
00:11:47.874 --> 00:11:49.709
I did have it the worst. though.

228
00:11:51.294 --> 00:11:52.378
-No.
-Yeah.

229
00:11:52.462 --> 00:11:56.216
-No. Are you fucking...
-The only daughter of an absolute maniac.

230
00:11:56.299 --> 00:11:57.943
-I was the baby.
-Are you fucking kidding? She...

231
00:11:57.967 --> 00:11:59.928
-No. she was fucking obsessed with you.
-Oh. Me?

232
00:12:00.011 --> 00:12:01.071
-Yes.
-She was obsessed with you.

233
00:12:01.095 --> 00:12:02.680
-No.
-Oh. no. No. no. no.

234
00:12:02.764 --> 00:12:04.224
-Yes. she was.
-You know what?

235
00:12:04.307 --> 00:12:07.268
It should be illegal
for a mother to have a daughter.

236
00:12:07.352 --> 00:12:09.705
-It should be illegal for a mother...
-Yeah. yeah. it should.

237
00:12:09.729 --> 00:12:11.356
They shouldn't let it happen.

238
00:12:11.856 --> 00:12:15.944
She was obsessed with you.
You were like her…

239
00:12:16.027 --> 00:12:17.528
Her little prince.

240
00:12:19.030 --> 00:12:21.699
You know. honestly.
her favorite was always him.

241
00:12:24.285 --> 00:12:25.954
[swallows] Yeah.

242
00:12:27.455 --> 00:12:28.498
Yeah.

243
00:12:31.459 --> 00:12:32.627
[chuckles]

244
00:12:32.710 --> 00:12:34.254
Richie. this is not happening.

245
00:12:34.337 --> 00:12:36.815
I'm sorry. but as your partner.
I cannot agree to this. I cannot.

246
00:12:36.839 --> 00:12:38.800
-Oh. okay.
-No. no. it's not possible. Richie.

247
00:12:38.883 --> 00:12:40.468
-I can make this possible.
-[Sydney] No.

248
00:12:40.551 --> 00:12:43.388
-I can!
